        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): scope agent wake targets",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nScopes agent-originated cron wake requests to the calling agent while preserving direct operator wake behavior.\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an inconsistency where agent-tool cron operations were scoped to the calling agent, but the wake action could still target a session owned by another configured agent.\n\n## Changes\n\n- attach the existing trusted agent-runtime identity to wake calls\n- reject foreign agent IDs and agent-prefixed session keys in the cron tool\n- enforce the same invariant at the Gateway handler and bind accepted calls to the authenticated caller\n- preserve unscoped operator calls and same-agent cross-session wake routing\n- add focused tool, Gateway client, and Gateway handler regression coverage\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe existing agent-runtime identity contract already scopes the other cron operations. Extending that contract to wake keeps enforcement at the Gateway boundary without adding config, protocol, storage, or migration surfaces.\n\n## User Impact\n\nAgent sessions can still wake their own current session or another session lane owned by the same agent. Direct authenticated operator and CLI wake requests retain their existing global targeting behavior.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/tools/cron-tool.test.ts src/agents/tools/gateway.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/cron.validation.test.ts` — 314 tests passed across two shards\n- reporter-shaped source probe — both cross-agent list and wake rejected; zero Gateway calls emitted\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/agents/tools/cron-tool.ts src/agents/tools/cron-tool.test.ts src/agents/tools/gateway.ts src/agents/tools/gateway.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/cron.ts src/gateway/server-methods/cron.validation.test.ts`\n- targeted `oxfmt --check` and `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` — clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n\n## Evidence\n\nBefore the change, the scoped tool rejected a foreign agent for cron list but forwarded the same foreign agent session through wake. After the change, the same probe returns:\n\n```text\nlistCrossAgent: cron list agentId must match the calling agent\nwakeCrossAgent: cron sessionKey must match the calling agent\nGateway calls: 0\n```\n\n## Notes\n\n- AI-assisted implementation and review.\n- The remote changed gate could not be launched from this checkout because no usable Crabbox or Blacksmith client is installed; PR CI remains the broad validation path.\n",
